    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This BadgeOS Add-on adds a shortcode to show a link. The user is awarded a specified achievement when the link is clicked. This shortcode is fully integrated with the BadgeOS shortcode insert button.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> You will need to install the free <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/badgeos/\" title=\"BadgeOS\" rel=\"ugc\">BadgeOS plugin</a>&trade; (version 1.4 or higher) to use the BadgeOS Community Add-on. The Plugin was tested up to BadgeOS 3.6.7</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/badgeos/\" title=\"BadgeOS\" rel=\"ugc\">Get the BadgeOS plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>This plugin was originally developed for the <a href=\"https://www.giz.de/akademie/en/html/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Academy of International Cooperation</a> of <a href=\"https://www.giz.de\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">GIZ</a>.</p>\n<h4>Contact</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://konnektiv.de/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Konnektiv</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload, activate and configure the free <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/badgeos/\" title=\"BadgeOS\" rel=\"ugc\">BadgeOS plugin</a> to WordPress.</li>\n<li>Upload &#8216;BadgesOS-Award-On-Click&#8217; Add-on to the &#8216;/wp-content/plugins/&#8217; directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.1.0 Sanitzed input, prepare for packaging and distribution</h4>\n<p>1.0.7 =<br />\nIntegration of internal attributes</p>\n<h4>1.0.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Support internal links by using the &#8216;internal&#8217; attribute</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Allow setting the target attribute</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>0.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
